# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MarkdownWeb — environment variables
#
# Local dev:   cp .env.example .env  and fill in real values
# Production:  set the same vars in your host
#              (Vercel project settings, systemd Environment=,
#               Docker --env-file, Caddy wrapper, etc.)
#
# Never commit .env. Never prefix server secrets with VITE_ —
# anything VITE_* is bundled into the client.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Admin bearer token for /api/mcp.
# Grants full access to every MCP skill (create/update/delete sites,
# mint scoped keys, etc). Treat like a root password.
# Generate a strong value with:  openssl rand -hex 32
MCP_ADMIN_KEY=replace-me-with-a-long-random-string

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Future (mdsites "hotel" / multi-tenant host)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When persistence moves out of the in-memory store, add the
# corresponding connection vars here, e.g.:
#
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:5432/mdsites
# S3_ENDPOINT=...
# S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=...
# S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
